author: Dirk Facer
title: Utah Utes football: Former Washington QB Troy Williams commits to Utah
text:
Troy Williams to join the Utes in 2016 after playing at Santa Monica (Calif.) College this season.
Upcoming Games Utah Football Utah football stats & schedule Utah @ USC Los Angeles Memorial Coliseum, Los Angeles Oct. 24, 5:30 p.m. 2  Days   19  Hrs   8  Mins   41  Secs More Coverage Utah notebook: Aiono is a center of attention Ute tight end position in good hands with Handley and Hampel SALT LAKE CITY — The Utah Utes have picked up a 2016 recruiting commitment from Troy Williams, a 6-foot-2, 210-pound quarterback from Santa Monica (Calif.) College.
Williams is a former Los Angeles area high school star who began his college career with the Washington Huskies. He redshirted in 2013 and played in five games (starting one) last year, completing 23 of 36 passes for 179 yards with two interceptions and no touchdowns.
Through five games this season at Santa Monica, Williams has completed 98 of 150 passes for 1,582 yards with 15 touchdowns and four interceptions. He’s also rushed for 133 yards and six scores.
